Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.86,0:00:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,June 19th.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.06,0:00:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I met with Franz Bonaparta for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.70,0:00:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,R.F. 1719.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.37,0:00:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A man with a quiet and calm demeanor.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.64,0:00:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,A refined and aristocratic look.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.41,0:00:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Dressed in a suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.18,0:00:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In the afternoon...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.08,0:00:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the children gathered for a book reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.82,0:00:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you want to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.73,0:00:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The border.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.93,0:00:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.26,0:00:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The Czech border.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.73,0:00:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.90,0:00:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.61,0:01:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In the afternoon, the children gathered for a book reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.38,0:01:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A very strange mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.72,0:01:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.42,0:01:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,P. Brevnov W.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.92,0:01:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,A spire on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.86,0:01:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,A weather vane on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.69,0:01:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Human dignity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.53,0:01:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,An experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.20,0:01:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A wonderful experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.53,0:01:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The deprivation of dignity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.00,0:01:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What country are you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.77,0:01:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked where you're from.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.97,0:01:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.54,0:01:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if a Japanese person would like this, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.78,0:01:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.88,0:01:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's left over from my lunch, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.01,0:01:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.32,0:01:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.78,0:01:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Just eat it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.38,0:01:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like you're gonna collapse any second now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.36,0:01:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife keeps nagging at me to lose some weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.46,0:01:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.36,0:01:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, eat up!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.26,0:01:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't, you won't make it through the long journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.17,0:02:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to end this journey already...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.23,0:03:36.95,Monster-Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(750,0)\pos(360,340)}The Never-ending Journey
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.63,0:03:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.34,0:03:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You let him go?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.00,0:03:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You just let Tenma leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.34,0:03:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.94,0:03:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you stop him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.78,0:03:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You already know he's a man you can't stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.85,0:03:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.08,0:03:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,On top of which...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.42,0:03:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we're in a dire situation with Eva Heinemann missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.15,0:03:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma even escaped from jail because of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.90,0:04:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That lawyer who called himself Baul...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.10,0:04:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He's most likely the same man who\Ntried to kill me at my clinic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.74,0:04:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,His objective was to get close to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.94,0:04:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and obtain my father's notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.41,0:04:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Those notes must be very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.02,0:04:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.49,0:04:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Where to?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.09,0:04:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,To where Tenma is headed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.22,0:04:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The "Red Rose Mansion"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.62,0:04:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.13,0:04:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My father's notes were full of meaningless descriptions...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.86,0:04:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don't think they were written in code.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.40,0:04:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.43,0:04:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,P. Brevnov W.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.90,0:04:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,P is for Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.77,0:04:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,W means west.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.78,0:04:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,A suburb of Prague, west of Brevnov!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.21,0:04:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A place where you can see "a spire on the left..."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.78,0:04:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,"and a weather vane on the right."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.12,0:04:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.55,0:05:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I just hope there's an eyewitness or someone who\Ncan help us solve the case at that mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.76,0:05:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's unlikely now...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.66,0:05:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.93,0:05:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,"In the afternoon, the children\Ngathered for a book reading."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.97,0:05:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That was described in the notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.44,0:05:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The children from back then could be our witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.01,0:05:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Verdeman.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.88,0:05:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I blamed you for letting Tenma go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.38,0:05:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I had been in that situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.52,0:05:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I would've done the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.95,0:05:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let's get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.39,0:05:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I was here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.80,0:05:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to live in this town...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.70,0:05:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.97,0:05:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Welcome home.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.21,0:06:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay, Nina?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.62,0:06:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.52,0:06:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's better if we give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.96,0:06:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how many times we do this, we still get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.36,0:06:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm sure I'll remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.33,0:06:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, my brother told me what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.43,0:06:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How he was taken away from The Three Frogs...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.04,0:06:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What he passed, and where he went.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.27,0:06:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He went past the train station...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.64,0:06:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and while he was watching the town on his left...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.68,0:06:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a trolley followed him along the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.76,0:06:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Please turn right over...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.66,0:06:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You shouldn't.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.33,0:06:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You shouldn't hide anything from him.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.93,0:06:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.17,0:07:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.61,0:07:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I-It's nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.88,0:07:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.98,0:07:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you recognize any landmarks?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.32,0:07:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.62,0:07:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's useless!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.83,0:07:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't remember something from so long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.60,0:07:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.20,0:08:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A weather vane on the right...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.28,0:08:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A church spire on the left...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.91,0:08:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.04,0:08:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The Red Rose Mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.18,0:08:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this the place?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.88,0:08:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.55,0:08:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.49,0:08:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I know this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.80,0:09:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm scared...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.48,0:09:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.16,0:09:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a door just appeared from inside the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.24,0:10:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.64,0:10:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.84,0:10:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.38,0:10:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.81,0:10:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You devil!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.32,0:10:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You devil!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.96,0:10:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The devil has been slain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.82,0:11:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.23,0:11:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back, Mr. Lipsky.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.70,0:11:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get any customers?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.71,0:11:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,No, business was as bad as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.04,0:11:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But the puppets are all so wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.61,0:11:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The one I'm making now is even better.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.09,0:11:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to see it soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.22,0:11:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I finish, you'll be the first to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.89,0:11:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time for me to go to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.20,0:11:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,At the restaurant?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.16,0:11:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I can't earn a living on just the puppets.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.13,0:11:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really sorry for imposing on you for so long...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.84,0:12:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.11,0:12:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.14,0:12:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Lipsky, there's something I want to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.01,0:12:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.85,0:12:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Three months ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.42,0:12:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,when you found me after I collapsed\Nand took me to a hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.29,0:12:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.92,0:12:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Why were you at that mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.26,0:12:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nina?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.36,0:12:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nina?!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.59,0:12:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nina!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.60,0:12:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Answer me, Nina?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.07,0:12:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nina!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.13,0:12:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What's wrong?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.37,0:12:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,When I go to that mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.61,0:12:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,images come to me for my work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.98,0:12:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I put it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.45,0:12:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But right now, more than that mansion, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.22,0:12:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.72,0:12:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.19,0:12:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You can stay here for as long as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.70,0:13:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.30,0:13:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I come in?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.14,0:13:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.40,0:13:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you should be out of bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.77,0:13:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.27,0:13:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.84,0:13:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is where the puppets are born.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.85,0:13:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Too bad I don't have any customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.45,0:13:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of story is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.52,0:13:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the story of a devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.33,0:14:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.86,0:14:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No, go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.90,0:14:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,A devil who leaves to find the dragon\Nthat threatens to destroy this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.93,0:14:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but almost dies in the middle of his journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.70,0:14:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,A young man passing by saves his life, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.48,0:14:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When the young man learns the true\Nidentity of the one he saved...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.51,0:14:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,he goes after the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.28,0:14:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the end of his journey, the\Nyoung man finds the devil...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.55,0:14:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and with a knife in his hand, slays the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.59,0:14:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's an interesting story, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.46,0:14:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody seems to like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.70,0:14:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Are you okay, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.57,0:14:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I would do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.77,0:14:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I would do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.14,0:14:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.21,0:14:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't let him do something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.65,0:14:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.78,0:14:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If you were human...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.08,0:15:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd save that devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.52,0:15:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.06,0:15:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he'd like this story.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.59,0:15:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.56,0:15:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,On this bookshelf...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.16,0:15:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all picture books.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.90,0:15:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Jakob Farobek.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.73,0:15:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.57,0:15:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Emil Scherbe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.57,0:15:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Monster Without a Name."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.68,0:15:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm surprised you know of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.98,0:15:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He wrote many picture books.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.21,0:15:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Jakob Farobek.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.88,0:15:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.28,0:15:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Emil Scherbe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.32,0:15:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all pen names of the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.36,0:15:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The man named Franz Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.46,0:15:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz... Bonaparta...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.27,0:15:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Human beings....{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.40,0:15:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}can become anything.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.57,0:15:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I wasn't a "superior child..."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.44,0:15:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I was driven away from the book readings.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.45,0:16:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Book readings?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.98,0:16:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,His book readings were held at the Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.29,0:16:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a student there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.52,0:16:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I understood what he was trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.90,0:16:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,"A deal! Let's make a deal!"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.10,0:16:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,said the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.40,0:16:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"No! Absolutely not!"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.70,0:16:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,said the man with big eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.37,0:16:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,"Yes! Let's make a deal!"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.64,0:16:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,said the man with a big mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.85,0:16:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The man with a big mouth's yard became a flower garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.42,0:16:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The man with big eyes became destitute and starved.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.26,0:16:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The man with a big mouth was cheerful every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.26,0:16:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He was full from all his ripened fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.53,0:16:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why he did not notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.10,0:16:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,His flower garden was wilting away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.60,0:17:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In the garden where no flower would ever bloom again...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.54,0:17:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the man with a big mouth cried and muttered...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.81,0:17:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,"I should never have made a deal with the devil."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.18,0:17:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The man with big eyes was so hungry\Nthat he thought he would die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.46,0:17:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Shedding tears, he muttered...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.53,0:17:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,"I should have made a deal with the devil."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.06,0:17:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,"A deal! Let's make a deal!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.17,0:17:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,said the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.90,0:17:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Man with Big Eyes, the Man with\Na Big Mouth," by Jacob Farobek.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.84,0:17:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Each Friday at three o'clock in the afternoon...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.78,0:17:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we would gather for the book readings.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.92,0:17:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We would sit around him...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.42,0:17:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and listen as he read us a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.82,0:17:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,With his kind voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.86,0:17:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,A very calm and kind voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.96,0:18:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And when he finished reading a story...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.53,0:18:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,he would ask us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.80,0:18:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,"The meaning of the story..."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.41,0:18:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,"do you understand?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.98,0:18:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I... I understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.51,0:18:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I also understood after reading it many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.38,0:18:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.38,0:18:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,he would take another picture book into his hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.82,0:18:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,"The God of Peace," by Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.26,0:18:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let's try reading this next.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.04,0:18:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as if I've come here for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.37,0:18:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it took me quite some time...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.48,0:18:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,all the memories have come together.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.29,0:19:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The god of peace is always busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.12,0:19:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He is too busy to look in a mirror...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.79,0:19:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and blows his horn every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.36,0:19:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The god of peace's horn makes everyone happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.93,0:19:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The god of peace is always busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.57,0:19:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He is too busy to look in a mirror...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.37,0:19:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and scatters magical water.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.04,0:19:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The magical water creates green mountains...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.01,0:19:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,ripens crops, and makes flower gardens grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.45,0:19:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The god of peace is always busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.18,0:19:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He is too busy to look in a mirror...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.85,0:19:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and gives everyone a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.02,0:19:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"Your name is Otto."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.32,0:19:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"Your name is Hans."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.69,0:19:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"Your name is Thomas."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.46,0:19:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"Your name is..."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.50,0:19:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"Johan."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.53,0:19:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan gave his hat to the god as a gift in return.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.61,0:19:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The god was very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.27,0:19:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he wanted to see himself wearing the hat...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.78,0:19:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,he stood in front of a mirror for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.11,0:19:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.18,0:20:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,what he saw in the mirror was a devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.42,0:20:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The devil spoke to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.62,0:20:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"I am you..."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.92,0:20:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,"and you are me."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.66,0:20:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh, no!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.93,0:20:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"No one can live in peace with a devil like this!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.36,0:20:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,"What should I do?"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.60,0:20:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the troubled god...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.94,0:20:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what he did?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.74,0:20:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured that out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.54,0:20:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.14,0:20:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what the "god" did after this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.45,0:20:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I do...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.22,0:20:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We finally meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.42,0:20:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.46,0:20:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.26,0:20:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.53,0:20:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think even you could have told us apart, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.97,0:20:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I am her, and she is me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.94,0:20:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I am you, and you are me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.94,0:21:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand everything now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.41,0:21:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Where we came from...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.68,0:21:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and where we are heading.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.05,0:21:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The weather outside is wonderful, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.17,0:21:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the flames engulf everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.56,0:21:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.76,0:21:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The god...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.85,0:22:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,pointed the gun...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.45,0:22:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,at his forehead!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.86,0:22:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Shoot me.{\i}
